l known for his own highly original system of metaphysics and ethics'a synthesis of Absolute Idealism, panpsychism and utilitarianism. The contributions gathered in this volume, written by philosophers of international reputation or by acknowledged scholars in their specialized fields of inquiry, engage themes in his metaphysics and ethics and provide a critical assessment of his ideas and arguments. In a concluding essay, Sprigge answers the most significant objections raised by his critics: the final result is an engaging dialogue on the perennial and most fundamental questions of philosophy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEthics, Modern. 0aFirst philosophy. 0aMetaphysics. 4aPhilosophie. 4aProzessphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAllard, James W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArmour, Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasile, Pierfrancesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBasile, Pierfrancesco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aClark, Stephen R. L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFord, Marcus P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForrest, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGale, Richard M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHannay, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonderich, Ted, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeslie, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLlewelyn, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadell, Geoffrey, econtrib